==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Circumvallation
<hw>Cir`cum*val*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The act of surrounding with a wall
or rampart.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A line of field works made around a
besieged place and the besieging army, to protect the camp of the
besiegers against the attack of an enemy from without.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumvection</ent>⟦br⟧
